Lazy Fish is decent sushi in the heart of Frederick. Good quality fish is sometimes hampered by rice that can be a little too pasty or sticky. Nice variety of rolls, but too many are fried rather than quality raw fish that is the hallmark of great sushi. Restaurant itself has a pleasant atmosphere and offers a full bar. If you want a good sushi restaurant experience for dining out, Lazy Fish is the spot to go to in downtown Frederick. If you want the BEST sushi and are willing to carry out, check out Kyo Sushi instead.

This place is a Frederick gem and one of our favorite date night excursions. The vibe is small, cute and cozy. The food is great, no matter what you pick - but don't eat so much you don't have room for dessert, because the fried cheesecake is so melt in your mouth good you're gonna regret sleeping on it.

Nice spot to watching down street in a snowy day and excellent craving food 💯💯💯 and price is so affordable for the quality, too.

I got take out the other day, and they accidentally forgot my soup. I work in the restaurant industry, so I fully understand that it does happen by accident. No biggie. I call lazy fish and tell them what happened. They offer me credit for it, but I paid in cash so no go. Not only do they drive to New Market which is at least a fifteen minute drive and bring me my soup for no charge. They gave me a coupon AND free dumplings for their mistake. I’ve been her dozens of times already. Not only is the sushi delicious, but the customers service is great too. I highly recommend it to everyone, and now I do more so after they went the extra mile for me.

We went to Lazy Fish for the first time tonight.  The food is outstanding.  We agreed that our waitress was the 1 in 100 perfect blend of always there the second you want something, but never hovering.  The only reason this isn’t a 5 is that the hostess is shockingly bad.  We got there, and a very unpleasant hostess tried to debate us for why we didn’t want to be the first people sitting upstairs.  We are pretty polite and told her sitting in an empty room makes us uncomfortable.  She seemed offended, and when she took us to a different table made sure we understood we needed to leave in 90 minutes.  We almost left in 90 seconds after dealing with her and we would have missed out on a wonderful experience, with a terrific waitress and delicious food.  We are good tippers and happy customers and loved our experience, but would probably turn around and leave if we went again and the same mean miserable girl was the hostess.

Food tasted good but both myself and my wife went out for the first time in months and we both got extremely sick, food poisoning sick. It was on 8/27 and we had both sushi and cooked food. Within 20 mins of leaving we both got really sick with cramps and stomach aches. This was our first time coming and unfortunately we won’t be back. In a time of Covid, one would think everything would be super clean but the masks and hand sanitizer did nothing to stop us from getting some contaminated food. 😒  Side note: Covid seating and procedures are completely ridiculous. Wouldn’t sit us at a booth by the window because they were trying to “maintain distance” so they sat us at a table right next to another couple and then seated someone 2 feet behind us. It’s really nonsense and in a small restaurant I feel you but you either are or aren’t social distancing and personally it doesn’t matter to me but even the people we sat next to said “you aren’t any further from us than you would be in the booth”.

This place picks and chooses what guidelines to follow. Me and my 4 friends got all dressed up to celebrate a birthday. We didn't even think to grab maks. When we got there we discovered we didn't have masks, but figured since we would be sitting at the table and remove them 5 seconds later there would be 0 issues. We walked up 2 flights of stairs and this place was packed, tables filled with people less than 6 ft apart, at this point I was like they shouldn't have any issues at all. The hostesses meet us with masks and asked if we had any we said we didn't and forgot them. They told us for them to allow us to walk 5ft to our table we needed masks. I asked if they provided any because we didn't have any. They said no and said to leave. Because they already got a fine for allowing people to just walk to there table. Very rude hospitality in there tone of voice and definitely not a place I plan to visit again. Especially since tables weren't even spread apart far enough to be following guidelines. Ruined my friends birthday.

Rating Lazy Fish is really a hard thing for me to do. The atmosphere is great and the menu is playful and innovative. This isn't your run-of-the-mill sushi place with everything drowning in spicy mayo. After looking at the menu, the designer cocktails and the creative specials (and pricing), I expected to be impressed.  I have been to this restaurant three times now and each time, sadly, I am not as impressed as I should be. I think my issue is with the quality of the waitstaff. I say this because tonight I gave this trendy downtown sushi joint one last try. And like the last two times I left feeling like I didn't have the best experience. Here's what transpired:  We ordered a selection of fun appetizers and cocktails: the mondu (dumplings), calamari and salmon carpaccio. My friends beer arrived on time but I was left to wait for my hot sake. Our first appetizer arrived...the salmon. I waited because I still didn't have my sake and I was hoping we could pick and share at our multiple appetizers whilst sipping on our cocktails. This never happened.  After about 15 minutes we decided to eat our salmon dish. A few minutes later our mondu arrived. Still no sake but the waiter never stopped to ask how things were. He simply placed the next appetizer on the table and wandered off.  We waited a bit but he never showed up to ask how everything was or if we needed anything. Another 15 minutes passed and he showed up with the calamari. At this point our experience is already 2/3 over and I don't have my cocktail. I ask again for my sake but switch the order from a large sake to small since we are pretty much done eating. He plays it off like this is no big deal and says oops I forgot it in the microwave. Eeeek. This is upscale sushi restaurant. At least sincerely apologize!  My hot sake arrives last. He could have asked my friend if he wanted another beer at this point but misses the mark again. We ended up eating individual appetizers in small, sad courses and for me with no cocktail. Calamari was fine. Mondu was fine. Salmon Carpaccio was too oily and I don't think it was sesame oil on it so it tasted like it was supposed to be salad but only oil was drizzled over it. I might not have noticed this if I had my sake from the start but I was deprived of this early on.  The waiter arrives at last to FINALLY ask if we need anything now that the meal is over. This would have been helpful early on or even mid-meal. We ask for our check and in my eyes this is a fail. This is now my third and last visit to this 'upscale' sushi joint. The service isn't worth what I paid for the food and my experience kinda sucked.  Still looking for a good sushi joint in Frederick that doesn't smother everything in spicy mayo but takes care of their customers. Please let me know if you've found one!!
